Setting Up Jenkins on EC2(Ubuntu)

Step 1: Install Java (Jenkins dependency)

sudo apt update
sudo apt install fontconfig openjdk-17-jre -y

Ensures correct Java version is installed
java --version

Step 2: Add Jenkins Repo & Key
Download and add Jenkins key
sudo wget -O /etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable/jenkins.io-2023.key
  
Add Jenkins repo
echo "deb [signed-by=/etc/apt/keyrings/jenkins-keyring.asc]" \
  https://pkg.jenkins.io/debian-stable binary/ | sudo tee \
  /etc/apt/sources.list.d/jenkins.list > /dev/null
  
Step 3: Install Jenkins
sudo apt update
sudo apt install jenkins -y

Step 4: Enable & Start Service
Enable Service
sudo systemctl enable jenkins

Start Service
sudo systemctl start jenkins

Step 5: Verify
sudo systemctl status jenkins

Step 6: Access Jenkins
Open browser:http://<EC2-Public-IP>:8080

Get initial admin password:sudo cat /var/lib/jenkins/secrets/initialAdminPassword


